caption: Excellent outside dining experience with a clever wine list and smart staff. Hanger steak was terrific and smoked fish plate was excellent.

Came here for a birthday dinner treat and did the tasting menu. AMAZING! the quality, the flavors, presentation, and overall quality was superb. Excited to be back in warmer weather and try the patio!

My girlfriend and I had an amazing experience at Forage on a recent date night. Every dish we had was incredible, and the portions were so generous that we didn't make it to dessert (even though we very much wanted to). Our server was very friendly, knowledgeable, and accommodating of dietary restrictions. We ate outside on a chilly night, but we were kept warm by the heaters on their patio and a mug of delicious coconut hot chocolate. We will be back soon!

In these pandemic times, I have found it is hard to track down a fine meal that stands up to takeaway. I tried a myriad of options, heartbroken and missing my moments of gustatory bliss. Then I tried Forage. My goodness, did Forage deliver what I needed, literally and metaphorically. I've done the 4 course takeaway meal twice and literally almost cried both times. It is the most beautiful food I've had in a long time. Every bite is swirling with expansive flavor, hitting notes like a well-mastered album on audiophile headphones. And the customer service is lovely, accommodating my allergy with caring grace. A peerless experience I definitely recommend.

One of the best restaurants I've been to in a long time. Everything is local and the menu is constantly changing plus they have great recommendations for what wines and drinks go well with each course. Definitely recommended to anyone that appreciates food made with thought and passion.
Tasting menu with wine pairing is the best deal in Boston.  Stan now imports his own wines, they're affordable and unlike anything you'll find in Boston

Whether a normal Thursday night with one of their amazing wine dinners or an actual special occasion, the people know how to make any night something to write home about. It's impossible to list a favorite dish because the menu matches what's seasonal and delicious but their wine and cocktail selection is great - trust them to recommend something you'll love!

Every time we've gone I've had at least a couple mocktails (I feel like if you're going to a place that actually puts them on the menu, you need to try as many as is reasonable) and have enjoyed all of them. Their food is also excellent. On our most recent trip we sat in the patio with heat lamps (Oct 2020) and were comfortable.
Despite the name, the food was brought to us at our table. It was delicious.
Wonderful food and atmosphere.  Excellent staff.

One of our favorite restaurants because we can order the vegan tasting menu and will always enjoy it even if the combinations are unexpected. They are fantastic at pairing wines where the food tastes better with the wine and vice versa. We aren't actually wine people and I walk away learning something without feeling like we were supposed to know anything beforehand.

Farm to table French dining at its finest. Amazing wine pairing options. Including natural wines, and rare French wines. 7-courses tasting menu with wine pairing is worth every penny. Outdoor patio in the back garden makes it for lovely dinner nights. The chef knows what he is doing and the service always Impeccable.

This restaurant is incredible! Would highly recommend to anyone and especially during covid. Their outdoor seating is intimate and beautifully lit with string lights and the food is very flavorful, delicious, and healthy! With only a handful of tables outside,  you really get to know all the staff and everyone was so friendly and accommodating!  At the end of the night we ended up chatting with the chef as well and he was excited to talk with us about his food. Every staff member was extremely kind and happy to be there. Had a great experience and will be back soon! Go to Forage!!
My wife got the Thursday wine pairing takeout for my birthday and it was so delicious!!   Each of the five courses were wonderfully flavored.  I can't wait for another excuse to go back!
Best patio dining in town
Some of the best local vegetarian food (and some non vegetarian as well, as this isn't actually a vegetarian restaurant, but they just do all their vegetable dishes so well!)

The place itself is very easy to miss. It's at the bottom of what looks like an apartment complex. Parking is also limited. The food is very, very creative. I'm neither a vegetarian or a vegan but every dish I had was full of style and flavor. Service was pretty good and everyone was very attentive and took time to answer every question we had. Would recommend and would come back

Exceptional. The BBQ duck is roasted then braised & honestly tastes like juicy bacon duck! The mussels are to die for too & everything’s locally sourced! Beach rose ice cream made in house. Super glad we live so close. Nice neighborhood vibes, super gifted chef, (apparently always pickling or brewing something), & fun waiter crew! We’ll def be back.
Small cozy restaurant with nice staff. You can accommodate all kinds of food references.

First of all, all the dishes were good on their own and you could taste that it was good ingredients. Service and cocktails were also more than fair. The Valentine's day menu was interesting but doesn't justify the price tag ($85 per person) for a small salad, a lobster mole (we didn't understand what the sauerkraut had to do with seafood or mexican cuisine and didnt pair well with the rest of the dish) and a custard.  I would have given 5 stars without the sauerkraut and if it was $75 instead of $85.
Good, but not mind blowing food. On the pricier end for quality.
The Chef is great . Food is very creative and tasty. Highly recommend.
Delicious food and nice ambience
Great experience, friendly staff
Great atmosphere. Amazing, exquisite, delicious food.
Very intimate place, food is very good, nice atmosphere. Highly recommended
Amazing! Get the tasting menu with the wine and you won't be disappointed! I had the vegetarian tasting menu and everything on it was delicious! And so was the bread!
Took forever between courses. Food was mediocre and insanely pricey.
Excellent. I've beed here quite a few times and everything has always been excellent. Food, wine, service and ambience are perfect.

A very well curated menu and interesting location.  Service was good, if a bit slow.  The wine list is very well put together and has some excellent selections.  Most of our party really enjoyed their meals, however the mushroom ragu I ordered was so overpowered with hot sauce that you couldn't taste anything else.  I would still recommend this restaurant based largely on the experience of my guests.

Forage is my new favorite restaurant! We went last night and were blown away by the amazingly delicious food and the superb service. Jeff took wonderful care of us,  taught us about Fernets (a type of liquor), and made everything easy. I had the mushroom appetizer and chickpea socca main dish. Both were amazing, which was especially notable since often restaurants struggle to make delicious vegan meals. The dessert was a deconstructed apple crisp with peach sorbet. Yummm... We're definitely going back. Maybe tonight!

We went for the chef's omnivore tasting menu, with cheese and wine pairing.   Outstanding from start to finish.  Even the bread was special.   Loved the service, and the moderate noise levels which is a rarity in Cambridge.   Location is atypical, situated in the basement of an apartment building.   But we loved the tiny bar putting out creative craft cocktails!
Tasting menu
Casey was AWESOME!!! FOOD outstanding, and the place is weird but eclectic

Both their food and drink menus are fresh and inventive. One of my favorite dishes I've had here was, I, believe, asparagus topped with dark chocolate and sea salt. Neither dark chocolate nor asparagus are among my favorite foods, but the chefs somehow made the combo work incredibly well.
Delicious meal with a variety of great vegetarian options. Creative flavors and lots of seasonal delicacies. Excellent service!

This place is a gem!  The food is absolutely fabulous with so many tempting options and a super fun cocktail menu. I went there for a (Jamaican) tasting dinner that was so fun and delicious.  The wines paired with the several delicious and creative courses worked quite well overall.  Looking over the rest of the menu made me decide that I definitely need to return to try more of their options.  Vegetarians and even vegan eaters will have no problem finding top notch, mouthwatering options here.  These offerings are designed with attention to detail and maximum flavor impact.  There are certainly great meat dishes available, but the exciting locally sourced, freshly prepared plant-based menu stands out. The chefs are undeniably talented and the staff is exceptional; professional and pleasant; no attitude.  The setting is comfortable and charming, but not large, so reservations are a good idea!
Best vegan 4-course I’ve had in the Boston/Cambridge area. Service was informative without being overbearing.
Delightful restaurant, great service, friendly staff. I had the veggie mushroom sausage as the appetizer, and the pasta main dish and both were excellent. You won’t regret visiting here.
Food was very eccentric.. Not suitable for everyones palate

The bartender is really top-notch; a bourbon cocktail called "130" was one of the best I've had anywhere ever. Appetizer of lettuces was tasty; however, there was a small wiry artifact that looked suspiciously like a hair. Entree: hangar steak cooked to order; broiled onions were a standout on the plate, but broccoli was too plentiful and too al dente. Sauce for the meat came in a minuscule cup; when more was asked for, another minuscule cup was brought. Ambience was outstanding: it was possible to converse at a comfortable level even when the small rooms were almost full, and music was always kept at an appropriate background level.
Beautiful food and excellent service!

Very impressive meal. The vegetarian tasting menu was delicious but we also got the scallops which were truly the star of the show.  The entire staff was extremely friendly and accommodating. We will definitely be back.

Small, quiet, intimate interior. Out of the hustle location. A perfect way to celebrate re-entry from a few weeks in the wild lands. Or if you want to be back. We had the most delicious meal and cocktails with a touch of nature feast for all our senses. They let us stagger choreograph our dishes building one shared dish upon another. Perfect waitstaff attitude, attention, and tempo. I will return.
Our favorite place for dinner or drinks in Boston. Fantastic wine selection, drinks, and food for a very reasonable price.

Very cute place. From the outside, it looks like it’s in an apartment complex. That means you’re in the right place! The service here was excellent, waiters were very kind, water was refilled quickly, and food came out fast and well-paced as we ate.  The food was mostly good, but one or two dishes weren’t as well-made as the rest. The ham was heavily over cooked, and so was very dry and chewy. On the flip side, the steak was cooked perfectly and well-seasoned.  I would also suggest that you order with restraint. We were a party of about 9, so we had a smaller preset menu (that we chose what to preset, and were able to customize a title, which was cute) that we ordered from. The waiter suggested two of each app for the table to try, and everyone’s own mains. The table comes with bread, and the cheese board is HUGE and has more bread. We felt like we ate a whole meal before we even ordered our mains. So, unless you’re feeling super hungry, definitely start slow and order more as you get through the meal.
This place is amazing. Service is superb. The food is unique and delicious. Everyday good like steak and bluefish with a twist. Mussels in a broth with actual spruce branches added for flavor.

The food and the service were both amazing. I honestly can't wait to come back. I got the vegan 4 course set menu and I loved every dish. They were also very accommodating to my other dietary needs, it was a delight.
Amazing restaurant with a very intimate vibe.  Food is great and the portions are large

Really liked this passionate and low key spot. We had a great time and the food was amazing! We will be back for sure. My wife loved the cozy setting! Parking is hard so, so take an Uber and enjoy a drink or 2.
In the old craggy space this little gem has a good combination of vegetarian and non-vegetarian items. Great for a romantic evening out

Came here with Cambridge friends on a Tuesday evening. This restaurant is in a residential neighborhood in the basement floor. I liked its coziness. We all ordered a set menu that came with paired wines. This night it was orange wines. The sommelier explained each wine pairing. Although they weren’t our favorite wines it was interesting. Other nights are scheduled with different wines such as Chilean ones. Check their schedule. The food by the way was very good. We could also have chosen our dinner from the regular menu.
An air-raid shelter with little charm and declining menu.
Excellent service and very good, adventurous menu.

The food here is good but the service and the wine are better. Frankly I’ve been here twice - both times in the hopes of a really high end meal - and both times I left with my expectations unmet. With that said it’s still pretty good but I find the food to be a bit bland

Very chic farm to table experience. Unusual menu, good wine list, a little skimpy on the cocktails but this is the republic of Cambridge so skimpy is chic too. While the restaurant has four parking spaces - they were occupied by the staff, grump, so parking is a serious problem for non-residents.Our dinner was for four seasoned eaters celebrating a new venture. You will not go home hungry. The owner visited our table, lovely, the waitstaff was attentive, the chef was more than capable and the ambiance was quiet and comfortable. Forage was as advertised - steak but without the sizzle which is fine but a little sizzle will go a long way toward establishing Forage's identity.

Forage is an incredible experience. It is a cute, quaint spot that had amazingly fresh and filling plates. I came for valentine’s day and was impressed with the vegan options and left feeling satisfied. Can’t wait to return.

Incredible valentines date experience . we got the 4 course vegan sample and every course was amazing , the service was top notch. We went in with no expectations and it was one of my favorite dining experiences in years.
Great food and awesome service.
Excellent food. Fun atmosphere. Got the vegan tasting menu. Will definitely be back.

Very good food and wine. Price is not unreasonable. Service is attentive. My only complaint is that its testing menu basically selects several dishes from the regular menu. So if you are willing to share dishes with your dinner companions, it makes more sense to just order from the regular menu and share - more variety and less money.

Hidden gem. Excellent gourmet eats. Tip, order your meat one level up on temperature. Medium well was still quite pink in the middle. The rare was almost raw. If I ever have to make a last dessert request, it would be the chocolate nemesis. Just divine. Happiness in a spoon.
Fun tasting menu. Definitely reccomended for a reasonably priced.exploration for good food.
Kind of pricey but truly farm-to-table. Interesting choices and outstanding service!
It's the sort of place where one of your courses is "carrot" and you know it will be one of the best carrots you've ever had. And it is. Cozy place, one of the best in Cambridge.

I own a farm-to-table restaurant in buffalo ny, and when I travel, I seek out other restaurants that practice the same mission. I was very pleased to find Forage and had a delicious meal. Everything was as promised and the ingredients where the purpose of the dish, not the chef’s ego. Staff was friendly and efficient. I had a great experience and would recommend this restaurant. Also, everything was seasoned perfectly!!!
Lots of pickled and fermented veggies with the food, it was all delicious

Giving this place anything less than 5 is madness, love this place! They use basic ingredients and create upscale yet unpretentious dishes. You can just tell the head chef knows what he is doing and has some serious thought/passion behind the menu. All the dishes have tremendous flavor. The cozy atmosphere and the fact it's hidden away on some residential side street makes this place a home run.
Creative, but tasty food in a classic new England setting
Had the full course vegetarian meal and it was great! Drinks are tasty as well!
Atmosphere is great. Food was fresh and delicious. Drinks were 👌🏻...
Cozy spot, great food and an excellent wine list

A cozy hidden gem just a short walk from Harvard Square; Forage offers elevated yet unpretentious fare with an emphasis on locally-sourced ingredients. The staff were very friendly and laid-back, and the 3-course “Sunday Supper” prix fixe menu was well curated, delicious, and super affordable! We look forward to trying one of the other weekly prix fixe offerings next time we’re in town.
Delicious.
Everything we ordered was excellent.
Such a creative menu! Food was delicious!

This place is truly a hidden gem and should be on anyone's short-list. From the exterior of the building, to the cocktails, to the service, to the chef's tasting menu... everything was impeccable and adventurous. Not a single bite was wasted.
An exceptional meal to say the least. The ambiance is simple and the restaurant is located in the basement of a building.
I liked that the wait staff was laid back and let me enjoy my time with friends.  The drinks were creative and the food was daring.  Had a great time.
Cozy. The food is really nice, especially the tasting plates. Nice ambience for a couple/ date or a catch up with friends.
Great food. Great wine and cocktail menu. Onsite free parking.  2 thumbs up.
Delicious food, great cocktails, interesting well thought out wine list. Knowledgeable friendly staff. Dessert was yummy too!! Highly recommend.
Wonderful dining experience featuring natural, locally sourced foods and some unusual offerings.
username: Ellen & Barry Levy Real Estate Gurus

caption: The experience wasn't all that memorable. The staff wasn't very knowledgeable about the wine, the food was overseasoned and unbalanced and the wait (post ordering our entrees) was way too long. Might consider returning in the Fall -- maybe the ingredients will be better then.
Wonderful little place, not too casual, not overly fancy. Loved everything I tried here. Our waiter was knowledgeable and I enjoyed learning about the organic wines we tried.
Delicious food, wonderful ambiance, and the friendliest, most helpful staff I’ve ever encountered. Can’t wait to go back!

Tonight was the third time I’ve left Forage absolutely blown away with how great the food and service was. Can’t recommend this place enough — every bite is bursting with freshness and creativity! Great cocktails and really friendly staff too!

Cocktails were excellent. Dinner was good. Innovative dishes with interesting ingredients, but for the price, the finishing touches didn't do it. The noise made conversation hard and our tiny corner table was awkward at best and nearly impossible for cutting a steak, plus the bench was too low.
Farm to table-ish. Great food and service!
Fantastic meal with great service!
By all means the food was decent with no glaring flaws but no dish stood out or wowed me. The service and the drinks were good but I thought it was a bit expensive relative to the quality I expected.
Parking is difficult. I had the tasting menu, two entrees, two apps,and a dessert. They were all alright.
A fancy treat
Amazing culinary experience with fantastic seasonal flavours that made for a great farm (and forage) to table adventure!
Creative farm-to-table food in a cosy space, interesting wines, good service, reasonable prices.  The Tuesday night wine dinners are a bargain.
A cozy place with good food.
Delicious. Fun. Quaint.

This place was a true find. The location may be a bit strange, but it's worth the trip. Every dish we had was not only delicious, but also very creative. Not to mention the cocktails were unique and delicious.

A farm to table sort of fare. But exquisitely done, with knowledgeable and friendly servers, equals an amazing dinner in a cozy subterranean dining room. I had the omnivore tasting menu and it was fantastic. Simply delicious. Looking forward to returning and trying the homemade pasta and other interesting dishes.
Delicious and simple.
Omnivore tasting menu with wine pairing was perfectly balanced. Can't wait to try a Monday night 6 course vegetarian tasting!
Great small plates and fantastic cocktails and non-alcoholic options. Can't wait to try their entrees.

Home to many prior restaurants, this lower level newborn is a worthy successor to many of those that have gone before. Only now it has a full bar, a nice selection of wines, and - as always - cheerful and competent staff. The food is excellent, much of it locally provided. The menu offers excellent value for four course tasting, and the wine pairings are great value (and good wines!). This restaurant, started by three well known locals from other restaurants, deserves to be a success.
Great wine and cocktail list. Staff is super friendly and acomadating. Such a cool hidden gem.
Intimate dining. .chef is outstanding
The dishes were ok but not worth the price charged.
Enjoyable prefixe vegetarian option, non alcoholic cocktails are a nice touch. Good quality food, presentation also good, small place and parking will require a short walk.
Best in town -- no one approaches the creativity and rigor these people do. So, so fresh. I love the thinking and the execution.

Dinner was nice.  Everything was fresh.  Cocktails and beers were great.  Great service. The pickled vegetables were good. The ribs and hanger steak were OK,  just a little bland for our taste. The sides for both dishes were very tasty.  Desert was delicious.  Definitely will try them again this winter.

We had a fabulous meal last night at Forage. I'm always a little suspicious of an over--emphasis on local foods (and the implicit assumption, sometimes false, that they have less embodied energy) but Forage pulled off a great series of dishes without any of that annoying pretension. We especially liked the Cured Char appetizer with the char, sea cabbage, and hemlock tips--delicious! The lamb and the maltagliate were also excellent. The wait staff was attentive without being invasive.
